    S:gt.blockmachines.extremeheatexchanger.name=超大型熱交換器
    S:gt.blockmachines.extremeheatexchanger.tooltip=Machine Type: §eHeat Exchanger, EHE§r\nInputs are §cLava§7, §cHot Coolant§7, §cHot Solar Salt§7, or §cPlasma\nOutputs are §9Pahoehoe Lava§7, §9IC2 Coolant§7, §9Cold Solar Salt§7, or §9Molten Metal\nConverts distilled water into §rSH Steam§7 or §rSC Steam§7 in the process\nOutputs §rSC Steam§7 if the input rate of hot fluid is above a certain §dthreshold\nExplodes immediately if it runs out of distilled water\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cLava§7 | SC Threshold §d80,000 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c160,000 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r640,000 mB/t SC Steam\n§cHot Coolant§7 | SC Threshold §d8,000 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c16,000 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r160,000 mB/t SC Steam\n§cHot Solar Salt§7 | SC Threshold §d1,600 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c3,200 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r160,000 mB/t SC Steam\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cPlasma§7 always outputs §rDense SC Steam§7 regardless of input rate\nThe max input and output rates depend on the plasma's density (EU/L)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nA circuit in the controller lowers the SC threshold at the cost of steam\n§d-1.5%§7 SC Threshold and §r-1.5%§7 steam output per circuit over 1\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.extremeheatexchanger.tooltip_secondary=   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   25x§7 - §6120x §r§7Robust Tungstensteel Machine Casings\n§6   72x §r§7Tiered Glass (EV+)\n§6   48x §r§7Pressure Resistant Wall\n§6   60x §r§7Tungstensteel Pipe Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hot fluid, front center casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Distilled water, any bottom layer casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Cold fluid, back center casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7SH Steam/SC Steam, any top layer casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.fix.name.remover.name=ネームリムーバー
    S:gt.blockmachines.fix.name.remover.tooltip=Removes various NBT tags as well as covers.\n \n§nFirst Slot§r\nThe item you want to strip of NBT\n \n§nSecond Slot§r\nOne of the following circuits:\n§lCircuit 1:§r  Attempt to fix broken ores by removing the Display Name tag\n§lCircuit 3:§r  Remove Railcraft stacking tag\n§lCircuit 4:§r  Remove Anvil repair tag\n§lCircuit 5:§r  Remove Dye from Leather armor\n§lCircuit 6:§r  Remove Spray color from GT items\n§lCircuit 7:§r  Remove Muffler Upgrade from GT machines\n§lCircuit 24:§r  Remove everything including covers. Be careful you won't recover the covers!\n \n§lNo Circuit:§r Remove everything except covers
