    S:gt.blockmachines.lftr.controller.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eReactor§r\nController Block for the Liquid Fluoride Thorium Reactor\nProduces energy and new elements from Radioactive Beta Decay!\nInput LFTB and a molten salt as fuel, and match the 4 Buffered Dynamo Hatches:\nLFTR Fuel 1 (4 EV Hatches), LFTR Fuel 2 (4 IV Hatches), LFTR Fuel 3 (4 LuV Hatches)\nIf using better hatches for a worse fuel, only 1 hatch will output EU\nOutputs U233 every 10 seconds, on average, while the reactor is running\nCheck NEI to see the other 3 outputs - they differ between fuels\n§54000 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.lftr.controller.single.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§64§7x§67§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   27x §r§7Hastelloy-N Reactor Casing (minimum)\n§6   26x §r§7Reactor Shield Casing (minimum)\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Top or bottom layer edges\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Top or bottom layer edges\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Top or bottom layer edges\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Top 3x3\n   All dynamos must be between EV and LuV tier.\n   All other hatches must be IV+ tier.\n   4x Output Hatches or 1x Output Hatch (ME), 1+ Input Hatches\n   4x Dynamo Hatches, 4x Mufflers\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.linear_accelerator.name=線形加速器
    S:gt.blockmachines.linear_accelerator.tooltip=Machine Type: §eParticle Accelerator, LINAC§r\nAccelerates charged particles to higher energies by running them through an electric field\nElectrically neutral particles are therefore unaffected\nUse a §bportable scanner §7for info about the input/output of this multiblock\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nIncreasing Structure Length increases output §9Beam Energy§7 but decreases §cBeam Focus§7\nRequires §fLength * kL/s §7of §bcoolant§7 for operation\n§cBeam Focus§7 loss can be mitigated more effectively with lower temperature §bcoolant\nValid coolants:\n  §bLiquid Nitrogen§7 : §690K\n  §bLiquid Oxygen§7 : §690K\n  §bCoolant§7 : §660K\n  §bSuper Coolant§7 : §61K\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§9Output Beam Energy§7§f = max(§eV§f, 50) * 10^§cIE\nwhere §eV§f = (Length - 1) * cbrt(§2Machine Voltage§f) / 4\nand §cIE §f= 1 + min(§dInput Beam Energy§f, 7500) / §aMaximum Particle Energy\n§cInput Beam Energies§7 higher than 7500keV are treated as if they are 7500keV\n§aMaximum Particle Energy§7 refers to values in the Source Chamber Tooltip\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cOutput Beam Focus§7§fdepends on the relation between §eInput Beam Focus§f and §3Machine Focus§f\nwhere §3Machine Focus§f = min(max((-0.9 * (Length-1) * 1.1^(0.2 * §6Coolant Temperature§f) + 110), 5), 90)\nIf §eInput Beam Focus§f > §3Machine Focus§f, §cOutput Beam Focus§7§f = (§eInput Beam Focus§f + §3Machine Focus§f)/2\nIf §eInput Beam Focus§f <= §3Machine Focus§f, §cOutput Beam Focus§7§f = §eInput Beam Focus§f * §3Machine Focus§f/100\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.linear_accelerator.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§67§7x§619-83§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   325x§7 - §61285x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Casing\n§6   148x§7 - §6852x §r§7Coolant Delivery Casing\n§6   127x§7 - §6703x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Glass\n§6   56x§7 - §6312x §r§7Superconducting Coil Block\n§6   156x§7 - §6732x §r§7Electrode Casing\n§6   47x §r§7Grate Machine Casing\n§6   48x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (LuV+)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 2\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 2\n§f   Beamline Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Beamline Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 4\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
