    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.assembler.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBEC Assembler, Observation Array§r\n§7Supplies nanites, power, and condensate to §6Observation Array Teleportation Node§6s§7.\n§7Nanites must be stored in a §6Nanite Containment Bus§6§7.\n§7Left-click the observation array controller with a data stick to save its connection info.\n§7Different types of nanites can be mixed, but the effective tier will be the §nlowest§7 of all provided nanites.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7§6Observation Array Teleportation Node§6s§7 will stall if they request more power than the observation array can provide.\n§7A recipe's condensate can be supplied at any time during its crafting.\n§7The recipe will fail if condensate is not supplied by the end.\n§7Crafting speed will be reduced if the network contains condensate that is not requested by the recipe.\n§7If there are more than §c3§7 unrequested condensates in the network while a teleportation node is running, the craft will §c§nimmediately fail§c§7.\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.assembler.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §629§7x§629§7x§629§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n§6   839x §r§7Coherence-preserving Plasma Conduit\n§6   1290x§7 - §61308x §r§7Electromagnetically-isolated Casing\n§6   190x §r§7Fine-structure Constant Manipulator\n§6   114x §r§7Electromagnetic Waveguide\n§6   120x §r§7Cyclotron Coil\n§6   256x §r§7Advanced Fusion Coil II\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Multi-Amp Energy Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Laser Target Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Bose-Einstein Condensate Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 2)\n§f   Nanite Containment Bus: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.diode.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBEC Diode, Storage Bus§r\n§7§b§lMaxwell's Demon's Big Brother§b§7\n§7Controls the flow of condensate in the network.\n§7Condensate that is present in the left hatch's network will be exposed to the right hatch's network.\n§7The opposite is not true; condensate can only flow in one direction.\n§7A §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Entanglement Apparatus§6§7 can only push condensate from the right hatch into the left hatch.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Consumes §a1A UIV§7 while active, regardless of the network's status.\n§7Using a §6Machine Controller Cover§6§7 on the controller will enable or disable transfers.\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.diode.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §617§7x§611§7x§611§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n§6   259x§7 - §6269x §r§7Electromagnetically-isolated Casing\n§6   84x §r§7Coherence-preserving Plasma Conduit\n§6   24x §r§7Cyclotron Coil\n§6   40x §r§7Advanced Fusion Coil II\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Multi-Amp Energy Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Laser Target Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Bose-Einstein Condensate Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 3)\n§f   gt.machine.bec.hatch.bec: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 2)\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.generator.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBEC Generator, Condensate Entangler§r\n§7Converts Prepared Condensate into Entangled Condensate.\n§7Entangled Condensate can only be transferred via a §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Conduit§6§7.\n§7Condensate will be processed even if there is no space in the network.\n§7Condensate can only be stored in a §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Containment Field§6§7.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Performs complex parallels.\n§7Consumes as much Prepared Condensate as possible, depending on how much EU/t is supplied.\n§7Machine processing time is the max duration of all active recipes.\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.generator.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §619§7x§619§7x§634§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front Center\n§6   254x§7 - §6271x §r§7Electromagnetically-isolated Casing\n§6   184x §r§7Coherence-preserving Plasma Conduit\n§6   92x §r§7Advanced Fusion Coil II\n§6   84x §r§7Electromagnetic Waveguide\n§6   238x §r§7Fine-structure Constant Manipulator\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing in the first slice (Hint: 1)\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing in the first slice (Hint: 1)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing in the first slice (Hint: 1)\n§f   Multi-Amp Energy Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing in the first slice (Hint: 1)\n§f   Laser Target Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing in the first slice (Hint: 1)\n§f   Bose-Einstein Condensate Hatch: §7The center casing in the last slice (Hint: 2)\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.io-node.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBEC I/O Node, Input bus, Output bus§r\n§7Teleports items into and out of the §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Observation Array§6§7.\n§7Recipe logic is the same as all other multiblocks.\n§7Condensate does not have to be present for a recipe to start.\n§7Right-click the controller with a programmed data stick to link it to the observation array.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Each item slot in a recipe has an associated nanite tier.\n§7For the teleportation node to progress through an item slot, it must receive a nanite with the same or higher tier.\n§7Excess nanites linearly increase the speed at which recipes are crafted.\n§7This multiblock's EU/t remains constant even when it is paused, stalled, or slowed down.\n§7This multiblock does not overclock.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7The §6Nanite Detector Hatch§6§7 can be used to detect the teleportation node's requested nanites.\n§7The §6Teleportation Node Controller Hatch§6§7 can be used to temporarily pause the teleportation node.\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.io-node.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §619§7x§619§7x§619§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n§6   149x §r§7Coherence-preserving Plasma Conduit\n§6   200x§7 - §6264x §r§7Electromagnetically-isolated Casing\n§6   156x §r§7Fine-structure Constant Manipulator\n§6   192x §r§7Advanced Fusion Coil II\n§6   224x §r§7Electromagnetic Waveguide\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Nanite Detector Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n§f   Teleportation Node Controller Hatch: §7Any Electromagnetically-isolated Casing (Hint: 1)\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multi.bec.storage.tooltip=Machine Type: §eBEC Storage, Entangled Condensate Storage§r\n§7Contained condensate is exposed to all observation arrays on the current network.\n§7Condensate routing can be controlled by using a §6Bose-Einstein Condensate Maxwell Gate§6§7.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Storage capacity is controlled by the field strength.\n§7The field strength is configurable in the UI. It can also be set by a computer.\n§7§61§7 unit of field strength can store §61L§7 of condensate, and consumes §61§7 EU/t.\n§7When multiple containment fields are present on a network, injected condensate is split based on their capacities.\n§7§8§m-----------------------------------------§8§7\n§7Excess condensate can be inserted into the containment field, but it will quickly be §c§nvoided§c§7.\n§7When a containment field is overfilled, §c§n11%§c§7 of its condensate is deleted each second.\n§7If a containment field shuts down at any point, its contents will be §c§nvoided§c§7.\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Recursive Pineapple§r§7
