    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oredrill1.tooltip=Machine Type: §eMiner, MBM§r\nUse a Screwdriver to configure working area\nMaximum area is 6x6 chunks (96x96 blocks)\nIn chunk mode, working area center is the chunk corner nearest to the drill\nUse Soldering iron to turn off chunk mode\nUse Wire Cutter to toggle replacing mined blocks with cobblestone\nGives ~3x as much crushed ore vs normal processing\nFortune bonus of 4. Only works on small ores\nMinimum energy hatch tier: §6MV§r\nBase cycle time: 12 seconds\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.oredrill1.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§67§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§f   Solid Steel Machine Casing: §7form the 3x1x3 Base\n§f   Solid Steel Machine Casing: §71x3x1 pillar above the center of the base (2 minimum total)\n§f   Steel Frame Boxes: §7Each pillar's side and 1x3x1 on top\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7MV+, Any base casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any base casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Mining Pipes, optional, any base casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Drilling Fluid, any base casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any base casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
