    S:gt.blockmachines.solartower.controller.tier.single.name=ソーラータワー
    S:gt.blockmachines.solartower.controller.tier.single.tooltip=Machine Type: §eSolar Tower§r\nContributing Green Energy towards the future\nSurround with rings of Solar Reflectors\nThe Reflectors increase the internal heat value of the Tower (see below for formula)\nEach Reflector ring increases tier, the first ring is required for the Tower to work\nInput: Solar Salt (Cold)\nOutput: Solar Salt (Hot)\nEvery cycle (10 seconds), heat increases and all the Cold Solar Salt is heated\nConverting Cold to Hot Solar Salt reduces heat, equal to the amount converted\nThis conversion only happens if heat >= 30000 and controller efficiency = 100%\nIf there's more Cold Salt than heat, all the heat is used up and returns to 0\nThe heat increase is most efficient at exactly half of maximum heat\nMinimum efficiency at 0 or 100000 heat, maximum efficiency at 50000\nHeat Efficiency formula: ( 7000 - [|currentHeat - 50000| ^ 0.8]) / 7000\nHeat gain per cycle: numberHeaters * heatEfficiency * (10 + bonus)\nBonus: 1 ring  = +1, 2 rings = +2, 3 rings = +4, 4 rings = +8, 5 rings = +16\nTotal number of reflectors based on how many rings are built:\n1 ring = 36, 2 rings = 88, 3 rings = 156, 4 rings = 240, 5 rings = 340\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.solartower.controller.tier.single.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §615-31§7x§628§7x§615-31§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Top center\n§6   229x §r§7Structural Solar Casing (minimum)\n§6   60x §r§7Thermally Insulated Casing (minimum)\n§6   66x §r§7Salt Containment Casing (minimum)\n§6   60x §r§7Thermal Containment Casing (minimum)\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 2 (Min 1)\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 2 (Min 1)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint Block Number 2\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.source_chamber.name=粒子源チャンバー
    S:gt.blockmachines.source_chamber.tooltip=Machine Type: §eParticle Source§r\nCreates beams of Particles\nUse a §bportable scanner §7for info about the input/output of this multiblock\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cTakes 1 input bus OR 1 input hatch\nNEI shows the minimum §bEU/t requirement§7, Beam Focus, Beam Rate, and §eMaximum Beam Energy\nAll recipes last for one second\nThis upper limit is approached asymptotically as operating power increases\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEach §6Particle Type§7 has a §aMaximum Particle Energy§7\n§6Alpha§7 : §a8000keV§7\n§6Proton§7 : §a15000keV§7\n§6Neutron§7 : §a15000keV§7\n§6Electron§7 : §a5000keV§7\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nEach §dSource input§7 has an Associated §9Energy Ratio§7\n§dU-238 Dust§7 : §9999§7\n§dCalifornium Dust§7 : §9999§7\n§dTungsten Rods§7 : §90.1§7\n§dLong LaB6 Rods§7 : §90.3§7\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§fActual Beam Energy = min(§aMax Particle Energy§7, §6aeV§7)\nWhere §6aeV§f =  §eMax Beam Energy§f * (1 - 1.001^(§9-Energy Ratio§7 * (§cEU/t provided§f - §bEU/t required§f)))\nIn short, the §6particle beam's§7 energy is capped to the §aMax Particle Energy§7\nAny one recipe can only provide up to its own §eMaximum Beam Energy\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.source_chamber.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65§7x§66§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   56x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Casing\n§6   52x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Glass\n§6   16x §r§7Electrode Casing\n§f   Beamline Output Hatch: §7Hint block with number 4\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Hint block with number 3\n§f   Input Bus: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hint block with number 1\n§f   Output Bus: §7Hint block with number 2\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.spaceelevator.name=宇宙エレベーター
    S:gt.blockmachines.spaceelevator.tooltip=Machine Type: §eSpace Elevator§r\n§o%s\nCan be equipped with up to §a12 §7Space Elevator Modules\nMotor tier limits module tier and amount of possible modules\nEach module has their own space for IO, except energy\nEnergy is supplied to this controller and gets distributed\nStarting from §dMotor MK-III §7the structure can be expanded to fit §a24 §7modules\nMax module amount is §a6§7/§912§7/§d15§7/§618§7/§c24§7 for §aMK-I§7/§9MK-II§7/§dMK-III§7/§6MK-IV§7/§cMK-V§7 motors correspondingly\nDisabling this controller also pauses all modules\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9§dminecraft7771§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.spaceelevator.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §635§7x§643§7x§635§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center of the middle structure piece\n§f   Project Modules: §7Any Space Elevator Base Casing With Hint Number 2\n§6   800x §r§7Ultra High Strength Concrete Floor\n§6   593x§7 - §6785x §r§7Space Elevator Base Casing\n§6   620x §r§7Space Elevator Support Structure\n§6   360x §r§7Space Elevator Internal Structure\n§6   1x §r§7Space Elevator Cable\n§6   56x §r§7Neutronium Frame Box\n§6   88x §r§7Space Elevator Motor (tiered)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Space Elevator Base Casing With Hint Number 1\n   Uses sub channel §6motor§r§7 for §6Space Elevator Motor Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
